narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 111 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 111 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Only take it if you need it as a graduation requirement.

The Spanish department does an excellent job designing both SPAN 110 and 120. The course is accessible and requires only regular, conscious completion of assignments, which are very reasonable. Don't slack and you will do very well in this course.
There is way too much work in this class. All of the cultural activities were unnecessary.
SPAN 120 is a very fast paces intermediate level spanish class that covers multiple verb tenses and lots of vocab and grammatical rules in one semester.
This class made my semester markedly worse. Horrible.
